This paper is about improving neural conversation models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a method for incorporating distributional constraints to generate more interesting responses. This involves using a model of syntax and topics, as well as semantic similarity. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which specifically deals with NLP. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SD (Sound).
